# Approach


**According to question**
The child whose rating is higher than that of his left or right neighbors should get more candies than his neighbors and the total amount of candies should also be minimum.
```
// so we can say that 
if current_child_rating > left_child_rating or current_child_rating > right_child_rating 
then 
current_child_get_candy = max( left_child_candy, right_child_candy ) + 1
```

```
case 1:For the minimum amount of all candies, each child will receive the minimum amount of candy possible (each child must have a minimum of 1 candy)
case 2: Child with same rating can get minimum possible candies
```
```
case 3: when  current_child_rating > left_child_rating 
    then current_child_candy = left_child_candy + 1
```
**Let us take an example:**
arr = [1, 0, 2]
1. for index 0 : because he is the first and don't having left neighbor so we continue,
2. for index 1 : he is having left neighbor but because currnt child having low rating then left child he don'n get extra candy
3. for index 2 : he is having left neighbour and also high ratings then neighbor so he will get more candies then his neighbour 


```
case 4: when  current_child_rating > right_child_rating 
    then current_child_candy = right_child_candy + 1
```
now we go from right to left:
1. for index 2: don't have right child so continue,
2. for index 1: he is having right neighbor but don't have high rating as compare to his right
3. for index 0: he is have right neighbor and also high rating then right neighbor so he will get more candy more candy as compare to right neighbor

**but wait**...What if the current child has a higher rating than the left and right neighbors combined, and the left neighbor has more candies then the right neighbor? so to solve this problem we take max candy + 1
```
update case 4 : 
when  current_child_rating > right_child_rating 
    then current_child_candy = max (current_child_candy, right_child_candy + 1)
```
And finally we'll add all the candy and return it.



# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int candy(vector<int>& ratings) {        
        int n = ratings.size();
        int total_candies =0;
        vector<int>candy(n,1);
        // case 1: Each child will get minimum 1 candy
        // case 2: children with same rating will get minimum candy.

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            // case 3: currend child having more rating left neighbor then he get more candy then left neighbor
            if( ratings[i] > ratings[i-1]) 
                candy[i] = candy[i-1]+1;
        }

        for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--){
            // case 4: current child having more rating then right neighbor then he will get more candy then right child
            if( i<n-1 and ratings[i]>ratings[i+1])
                arr[i]=max(candy[i], candy[i+1]+1);

            total_candies += candy[i];
            // add all the candies
        }

        return total_candies;
    }
};
```

